23 A BILL
24 TO BE ENTITLED
25 AN ACT
26
27 Relating to utilities; to add Sections 37-1-32.1 and
28 37-1-81.1 to the Code of Alabama 1975; to require the Public
Page 1

37-1-81.1 to the Code of Alabama 1975; to require the Public
HB475 INTRODUCED
29 Service Commission to hold annual meetings; to require notice
30 of the meetings; to authorize the impeachment of members of
31 the commission for failure to hold meetings or provide notice;
32 and to prohibit utilities from including certain costs in the
33 calculation or determination of rates or service regulations.
34 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
35 Section 1. Sections 37-1-32.1 and 37-1-81.1 are added
36 to the Code of Alabama 1975, to read as follows:
37 §37-1-32.1
38 (a) Consistent with its duties and responsibilities
39 under this chapter, at least annually, the commission, through
40 its staff, shall convene a public meeting with utility
41 representatives to provide information to the commission, its
42 staff, and the public on rates, cost trends, reliability,
43 resilience, general infrastructure investment plans,
44 competitiveness with peer states, economic development
45 impacts, and other regulatory issues the commission deems
46 relevant. These meetings shall be conducted in a manner that
47 facilitates public participation and provides a review of key
48 issues that the commission believes will be helpful to the
49 public in understanding issues that impact services under the
50 commission's jurisdiction.
51 (b) The commission, through its staff, shall provide
52 notice of each meeting to the public in compliance with the
53 Alabama Open Meetings Act, Section 36-25A-3.
54 (c) If the commission fails to convene a meeting
55 required by subsection (a) or the commission fails to provide
56 notice required by subsection (b), the failure shall
Page 2

notice required by subsection (b), the failure shall
HB475 INTRODUCED
57 constitute a willful neglect of duty and shall subject each
58 commissioner to impeachment pursuant to Section 36-11-1.
59 §37-1-81.1
60 (a) A utility that provides retail electricity service
61 may not factor the following costs into the calculation or
62 determination of a new rate or service regulation or a change
63 to an existing rate or service regulation charged to customers
64 of the utility:
65 (1) Costs incurred due to the utility providing funding
66 or grants to other persons or organizations.
67 (2) Costs incurred due to the hiring of persons for the
68 purpose of lobbying the Legislature or any other political
69 office or subdivision of the state.
70 (3) Costs incurred due to advertisement of the utility.
71 (b)(1) When an electric utility files a new schedule to
72 put in operation a new rate or service regulation or to change
73 an existing rate or service regulation, the utility shall
74 affirm that the utility has not included the prohibited costs
75 under subsection (a) in the calculation or determination of
76 the rate or service regulation.
77 (2) If the electric utility fails to make the
78 affirmation, the rate or service regulation shall be void.
79 (c) If the commission discovers that a utility has
80 included the prohibited cost under subsection (a) in the
81 calculation or determination of rates or service regulations,
82 the commission shall investigate the determination pursuant to
83 Section 37-1-83 and other powers of investigation granted to
84 the commission pursuant to this division.
